Hello to all,
Here I made this post because since July 1st, I've been having a bad trip on LSD,
I want to say that before this bad trip I was shooting 20 shells a day and I did some pretty heavy hits every two months with some serious drugs (Taz, coke, LSD, and all the rest)...For 3 years,
now I'm going to tell you how it's going.
a good week awaits me
We had planned with 3 colleagues to take 10gr of speed, 1gr of mdma and 2 bottles of lsd ,
Friday evening everything goes well
we have consumed 5gr of speed plus all the md,
saturday morning after a sleepless night I'm going to work just the morning from 9h to 12h in the afternoon ,
on n'a continuez,
I keep going on my own tapping shells and taking speed.
mid afternoon, evening arrives and 2 other colleague join us and we had decided to take LSD on the beach (personally I wasn't reassured),
a colleague held the glass for me with a drop from the lsd bottle
I hesitated at first then after I told myself come on I'll take it(something I shouldn't have).
the evening continued normally and the two so-called colleagues had decided to make us really go crazy...
on this famous beach there was a lot of people and one of the two colleagues said there's someone looking for trouble we're going to fight...
I tell myself I need to lower the product price because I can't fight like that
so i forced myself to resist the product,
la, la paranoia starts to invade me, all in making a mise en scène
the two other colleagues who hadn't taken anything starts to look for the guys who are after us
me being totally paranoid I keep telling myself it's going to happen at any moment,
time passes nothing happens.
brief we leave the beach and then we go to my place,
I ask them if the guys are following us,
He doesn't respond,
we get to my place and there he leaves us all in the lurch, all alone at my place with my girlfriend who was sleeping...,
I continue my bad all night
can't sleep, I'm thinking and at the slightest noise I grab a bat and leave...
the day rises and i start to fall asleep because i just came to realize that there is nothing,
the night passes normally,
I get up and I'm still under the effect of LSD and all
I tell myself it's normal
so we were on Sunday and the next day I had to work.
the day is passing normally
I tap some shells then I nap,
Sunday passes and Monday arrives
I still feel painted over,
I keep telling myself these normal things with the box that I have taken....
so at 14h I had to take the job
I eat a little and I take a lot of speed to feel good at work...
so I take the car and then I go to work
get to work, as soon as I open the store I start getting vertigo my heart starts beating at 200 and I feel like I'm going to pass out,
to reassure myself I'm going to buy some Snickers bars and something to drink,
after that I go back to work and another crisis...
panicked I apel my mom.. because the collegue wasn't there ....
after her mom brought me to the doctor
He asks me what I did and there I spill all my bag
and my mom took it pretty well finally she knows I was shady..
The Doctor tells me to wait for the product to go down, it will take a few months, and that's all,
I told him I had vision problems
I told him I had vision problems
He told me that it was normal too and that it will go down soon,
for my anxiety attacks, he prescribed me lizanxia, an anti-axiolitite finally against anxiety,
I take 1 in the morning 1 at night,
It calms me down but the voices in my head don't stop,
it gives me often a good headache...
after this Bad I've stopped everything no more bullets nothing,
My girlfriend doesn't understand what's happening to me and really couldn't care less
I fired him,
my colleagues also don't give a fuck so I fired them too,
at the same time I moved ,
I'm currently living with my mom, but I found an apartment.
but i can't live there because i have anxiety attacks .
In addition to that, I have a bunch of thoughts in my head
recently had suicidal thoughts.. voices that make me feel guilty or provoke anxiety crises.
Currently it's been 5 months today since I did this bad and in terms of my vision I still look behind a mirror
finally these trouble especially when it's sunny...
the voices in my head don't stop from morning until night...
my thoughts confuse me to force always doing the same
I feel like I'm living the same day over and over.
with all of that I don't recognize myself anymore,
I always have my job, I don't have any friends apart from 2 cousins and my brother who are far from me,
I work alone too
and so all day I am alone except in the evening when my mom is here...
I'm going to consult an ophthalmologist at the beginning of January, but I don't think it's going to fix things much,
actually I don't know what to do anymore except wait and maybe get out...
Thanks for reading my message and sorry for the spelling errors..
if someone has already lived this experience, can or can they give me some advice. thanks
Hello to you Cllaude271. To start, I don't take lsd.
I sometimes take some emphét' (speed) or pop some douille but not lsd, ketamine or anything else.
I think you should simply see another doctor or a toxicologist (I don't know if that's the exact term)
If after 5 months you're still dealing with this kind "of side effect" it's really bad.
So without wanting to panic you should see a toxicologist who I think will prescribe you treatment or emergency detox.
Otherwise, there are green numbers or specialized forums. Good continuation. Peace
Hi Cllaude271,
To have gone through the state you describe multiple times (due to various mixtures of chatters, micropoints, TAZ, keta, in fact, everything that passed through there),
if I can give you a piece of advice, it's simply to tell you that all of this is just psychological.
In general, the more you stress about these states, the worse they will get.
A very simple thing in these cases, you take deep breaths, you breathe slowly, and you settle in a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yes sometimes you can feel they're closing in on you).
After several months following a use, especially when you mix substances, you can experience effects, especially after a sudden cessation of substances.
Don't worry, it's just a matter of time.
But as Cllaude532 said, consulting a psychiatrist might also help you get rid of these voices that clutter your head.
Keep the catch, and stay positive.
Thanks to both of you for your responses
I will try to be patient,
